220 ÷ 2 = 110.

110 is also even, so divide by 2 again: 110 ÷ 2 = 55.

55 is divisible by 5: 55 ÷ 5 = 11.

11 is a prime number.

So, the prime factorization of 220 is 2² × 5¹ × 11¹.

Using the sum of divisors formula again:

Sum of divisors = (1 + 2 + 4) × (1 + 5) × (1 + 11) = (7) × (6) × (12).

