So, if \(a = 3\), then all roots are real, real and equal in this case. If \(a > 3\), then there are two distinct real roots from the quadratic, which in turn would give three real roots overall (including \(x = -1\)). So, the minimal value is indeed 3, as when \(a\) is exactly 3, you have a triple real root, and for \(a > 3\), you have three distinct real roots.

