Then, \(d = 3*(-2) = -6\)

Now, equation 2: \(c + e + b d = 18\). Substituting \(c = 3\), \(e = -9\), \(b = -2\), \(d = -6\):

\(3 + (-9) + (-2)*(-6) = 3 - 9 + 12 = 6\)

But equation 2 requires this to be 18. So, 6 ≠ 18. So, this doesn't work.

