\[
\frac{54}{3} \times 1 = 18 \text{ dollars}
\]

They sold 20 cupcakes at $2 each, giving them a revenue of:
\[
20 \times 2 = 40 \text{ dollars}
\]

They sold 35 brownies at $1 each, giving them a revenue of:
\[
35 \times 1 = 35 \text{ dollars}
\]

