\[
2x^3 - 30x^2 + 174x - 370 = 8x^3 - 120x^2 + 600x - 1000
\]

Bringing all terms to one side:
\[
0 = 6x^3 - 90x^2 + 426x - 630
\]

Factoring out the common factor:
\[
6(x^3 - 15x^2 + 71x - 105) = 0
\]

