\[
\text{Perimeter of octagon} = 8 \times s
\]
where \( s \) is the side length of the octagon. We know this perimeter must equal 96 cm:
\[
8s = 96
\]

Solving for \( s \):
\[
s = \frac{96}{8} = 12
\]

Thus, the length of each side of the octagon is \(\boxed{12}\) centimeters.
