Wait, another approach: Let me consider the roots of \( z^4 + z^2 + 1 = 0 \). If all roots are \( n^{\text{th}} \) roots of unity, then each root satisfies \( z^n = 1 \). So, the minimal such \( n \) is the least common multiple of the orders of all the roots.

