- \( e^{-i2\pi/3} = -\frac{1}{2} - i\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \).

Yes, that's correct.

So, all four roots are \( e^{\pm i\pi/3} \) and \( e^{\pm i2\pi/3} \). These are all 6th roots of unity, right?

