I remember that when you raise a power to another power, you multiply the exponents. So, (a^b)^c = a^(b*c). So, applying that here, if I have (2^2)^x, that should equal 2^(2x). And we want that to equal 2^3. So, setting the exponents equal, 2x = 3. Therefore, x = 3/2.

